Subject: [PATCH 0/9] arm64: dts: allwinner: add initial A733/Cubie A7S support

Draft-only public review export. Do not send this series upstream as-is.

This series prepares minimal platform bring-up for the Allwinner A733 SoC
and Radxa Cubie A7S board:

- Radxa Cubie A7S board compatible
- initial A733 CCU binding and driver
- A733 pinctrl binding and driver
- A733 MMC compatible
- initial A733 SoC DTSI
- Cubie A7S DTS with UART0 console and MMC0 storage
- explicit Allwinner sun60i MAINTAINERS pattern

Ethernet, VPU/Cedrus, display, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and other board
peripherals are intentionally out of scope.

Known blockers before upstream submission:

- Junhui Liu has posted an RFC A733 CCU/PRCM series:
  https://lore.kernel.org/r/20260310-a733-clk-v1-0-36b4e9b24457@pigmoral.tech
- Andre Przywara has posted an RFC A733 pinctrl series:
  https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250821004232.8134-1-andre.przywara@arm.com
- The CCU and pinctrl portions must be rebased on, coordinated with, or
  explicitly justified against that in-flight work.
- The expected sendable direction is a smaller board/SoC DTS series stacked
  on the accepted or current CCU and pinctrl prerequisites, unless subsystem
  maintainers ask for a different dependency plan.
- A hardware boot/runtime record is still required for the exact kernel,
  DTB, board, and command line before runtime claims are made.
- Final human review must decide the submission disclosure/trailer policy
  according to current kernel documentation and subsystem expectations.

This export addresses the current public-review cleanup issues by removing
automatic coding-assistance trailers, adding the missing MAINTAINERS pattern,
using the author's contact in new binding maintainer blocks, adding asymmetric
CPU capacities, and replacing the irregular GICv3 redistributor size with a
normal 8-core window.

